<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="463" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,223,322]" pageId="2" pageNumber="463">
The subfamily is defined by the highly complex gonopods, in which a broad, comb-like branch replaces the flagellocoxites seen in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bollman" authorityYear="1893" box="[351,471,259,285]" class="Diplopoda" family="Striariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Striariinae">Striariinae</taxonomicName>
. The ninth legs are substantially reduced and the sternum, coxae and telopodites are fused. See also the Notes sections below, under the description of the new genus.
</paragraph>
